As for what the fuck this server thinks?  I used to give a damn.  I used to even consider myself part of this community.  But you know something, this server has some of the biggest fucking hypocrits there are.  <br>
<br>
I go out of my fucking way to help people.  You'd be hard pressed to find many people who don't like me (at least I think, if you don't like me most of you say it behind my back).  Fire and Fury and Resolution have always had issues about PR, because truthfully we need more players constantly.  We will always need more because with any raiding guild there is turnover, sometimes higher than others.<br>
<br>
As for PR, we've seen different types of PR.  In the past Fire and Fury has sponsored such rp events such as Tinkerfest, Resolution has led open raids on Plane of Mischief (back when it was hard to get there).  The community loves these guilds at these times, and then turns around and bitches about how &quot;uber&quot; they are and how they &quot;ruin&quot; this perfect little roleplaying community.  I'm tired of the bullshit and am willing to call the people on it.<br>
<br>
Half of the people &quot;bitching&quot; about ebay proudly wear their bazaar bought gear from zones they will never see, they happily accept rewards from things like Gore's old dueling competitions, or like the one I just held.<br>
<br>
Personally from this point on, I could give a rats ass what this &quot;community&quot; thinks of me.  I've been here since the beginning, given things of myself to it, and been given things out of it.<br>
<br>
The people that know me, know me.  The people who want to believe ANONYMOUS posters (and yes Cielo please redefine what the hell anonymous poster is, because right now its no better than allowing anonymous posters.  If you'd like an example of why that is so Ill do it for you).<br>
