<br>
I haven't seen the collective of FnF stand up here and say: We approve.<br>
<br>
A few people in FNF think its ok. A few people do not. A few people are on the fence, a few people do not care.<br>
<br>
I have said it once, and I'll probably say it a thousand times. One person does not a guild make. Their actions may reflect on their guild, and if the guild takes no action against them, it may also reflect on them, but I think all of us know by now that FnF is merely a sum of all its parts. Some of them are good, honest, civil people who I call friend. Others of them are fucktard assholes who have no consideration for others. I'm not going to hold something against one or two people, the actions of a few others. The problem here is that some of these folks desperately (or not so desperately) want to go to the end of the game and kill Quarm. They want to be the first that do it on this server. The guild closest to that goal is FnF. Many of them feel if they left FnF it will never happen for them, thus -- this bug/exploit/griefing issue is a non-issue for them. They expressed their displeasure, but in the end, its: lets just forget about it and move on. That's their right to do it, certainly. Me, I'd be tempted to move out and start a new guild on my own to try to get to that content. But thing is, its been done before, and many of those offshoots have failed. Most folks would probably feel that to do so, to break things apart at this stage in the game, would ruin their chances to do and see what they want to do.<br>
<br>
I can understand that. I may not agree with it, but its not my place to agree or disagree with a person's motivations. I think Zsu is right to tell folks that its not any of our buisness how people react to this or to peruse the internal matters of their guild. The only thing that matters here folks, that folks have lost sight of , is that some individuals, who happen to be in, or officers in guilds that have more than just them in that guild, are using and abusing an exploit, and causing other people harm. There's no need to attack the entire guild for that. *shrug* If you have to attack someone, attack the people responsible for causing the grief.<br>
<br>
